Africa U-23 Nations: Find out the South African Olympic squad
05 Nov 2019, 02:32 by Riham Bakir
Reham Bakir is competing in eight teams for the title of the African Under-23 Nations Cup, which will be held in Egypt from 8 to 22 November, and qualify for the Tokyo Olympics 2020 for the top three places. The first group to be played at Cairo International Stadium includes Egypt, Mali, Ghana and Cameroon. The stadium hosts Group B matches, which include Nigeria, Côte d'Ivoire, Zambia and South Africa. Yalla, Thabisu Munyani, Happy Machiyani, Terchos Malibi, Catlego Mohami, Kano Kubido; Middle: Sefo Mbouli, Athenkosi Dalala, Kopamilo Kudisang, Camuhilo Mahlatsi, Grant Magman, Tibohu Mukwena, Luther Singh;
